description:
&lt;p&gt;Working within our Information Governance Team you will work closely with our Head of IG, Data Protection Officer and SIRO to support the establishment of a proactive and integrated approach to information governance and the 2018 Data Protection Act to ensure that good practice is embedded across the organisation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the Information Governance Officer you would be working as part of a corporate team to continue to raise awareness of the new requirements of the GDPR and the Data Protection Act 2018, and to support the development of new working practices and guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will assist in the development and maintenance of Trust policies in regards to information security and information governance; assist in the co-ordination and administration of the Data Security Advisory Group meetings. You will also need to be an excellent communicator, willing to work as part of a team, and capable of using your own initiative with minimum supervision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must possess a comprehensive range of practical analytical, numerical and statistical skills (a degree level qualification in a relevant subject or appropriate NHS Information Management experience is desirable, but not essential).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder must also be computer literate with a good working knowledge of Microsoft applications.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Have a good understanding of current information governance&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience of writing policies, procedures and guidance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Knowledge of the General Data Protection Regulations&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Willing to come up with ideas and suggestions for new ways of working that will ultimately improve overall performance and service delivery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please refer to the Job Description and Person Specification for all essential and desirable criteria required for the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Full Time 37 Hours 30 Minutes/Week&lt;/p&gt;
